overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, including critical security vulnerabilities and broken Vercel
  deployments. The process involved systematically addressing lint errors,
  implementing secure HMAC-based session management using the Web Crypto API for
  Edge Runtime compatibility, and adding robust input validation and pagination
  to API routes. Key challenges included resolving PDF calculation bugs, wiring
  up UI elements, and updating the Zod schema for time validation. A significant
  hurdle was encountered with Vercel deployments failing due to a Next.js
  security vulnerability (CVE-2025-66478), which necessitated an upgrade to
  Next.js 16.1.1. This upgrade, in turn, introduced breaking changes in ESLint
  configuration and Prisma client initialization, requiring further adjustments
  to ensure build and runtime compatibility on Vercel. Finally, outdated e2e
  tests were updated to reflect the current application content. The outcome is
  a fully functional application with all security, bug, and deployment issues
  resolved, and all CI checks passing.
